paragraphs.title: Setup FSDS Connection
paragraphs.text:
import org.locationtech.geomesa.spark._

val dataFrame = spark.read
  .format("geomesa")
  .option("fs.encoding","parquet")
  .option("fs.path","s3a://optix-fsds/")
  .option("geomesa.feature", "exactAIS")
  .load()
dataFrame.createOrReplaceTempView("fsdsAIS")

paragraphs.title: Create a Temporary View for data in the Gulf of Mexico around the dates of Harvey
paragraphs.text:
%sql

CREATE OR REPLACE TEMP VIEW harvey as (
    select 
        * 
    from  
        fsdsAIS 
    where 
        /* Harvey formed on Aug 17 */ 
        dtg > cast('2017-07-17' as timestamp) 
        and 
        /* Harvey dissapated on Sept 2 */
        dtg < cast('2017-10-3' as timestamp) 
        and 
        st_intersects(st_makeBBOX(-100.3051, 15.5020, -73.6962, 33.8272), position)
)

paragraphs.title: Cache the Harvey Temp View
paragraphs.text:
%sql

cache table harvey

paragraphs.title: Number of Tankers in Gulf for month over Harvey
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select 
    count(distinct mmsi),
    vessel_type_sub,
    dtg
from (
    select 
        mmsi,
        date_sub(dtg, 0) as dtg,
        vessel_type_sub 
    from 
        harvey
    where 
        vessel_type like "Tanker"
        and 
        dtg > cast('2017-07-17' as timestamp)
        and
        dtg < cast('2017-10-3' as timestamp)
)
group by 
    dtg,
    vessel_type_sub
order by
    dtg

paragraphs.title: Number of Tankers around Houston for month over Harvey
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select 
    count(distinct mmsi),
    vessel_type_sub,
    dtg
from (
    select 
        mmsi,
        date_sub(dtg, 0) as dtg,
        vessel_type_sub 
    from 
        harvey
    where
        st_contains(st_bufferPoint(st_makePoint(-94.867089, 29.580314), 50000), position) 
) 
where 
    vessel_type like "Tanker"
group by 
    dtg,
    vessel_type_sub
order by

paragraphs.title: Min/Max Normalized number of tankers and fuel prices for month around Harvey
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select 
    /* Calculate min/max normalized values */
    dtg,
    ((nyh - min_nyh) / (max_nyh - min_nyh)) as nyh_norm, 
    ((usgc - min_usgc) / (max_usgc - min_usgc)) as usgc_norm,
    ((num_ships - min_num_ships) / (max_num_ships - min_num_ships)) as ships
from (
    select
        /* Prepare for min/max normalization */
        dtg,
        nyh,
        min(nyh) over () as min_nyh,
        max(nyh) over () as max_nyh,
        usgc,
        min(usgc) over () as min_usgc,
        max(usgc) over () as max_usgc,
        num_ships,
        min(num_ships) over () as min_num_ships,
        max(num_ships) over () as max_num_ships
    from (
        /* Get from the JOIN */
        select 
            /* Fill null values with last value to make graph continuous */
            ifnull(gas.nyh_value, last(gas.nyh_value,true) over (order by ships.dtg)) as nyh,
            ifnull(gas.usgc_value, last(gas.usgc_value,true) over (order by ships.dtg)) as usgc,
            num_ships,
            ships.dtg as dtg
        from 
            houston as ships LEFT JOIN gas
        on 
            ships.dtg = gas.dtg
    )
)
where 
    /* Cut off lead dates that have null fuel values */
    dtg > cast('2017-07-17' as timestamp) 
    and 
    dtg < cast('2017-11-3' as timestamp)
order by 
    dtg

paragraphs.title: Tankers Temp View

CREATE OR REPLACE TEMP VIEW tankers as (
    select 
        mmsi,
        /* convert to 00:00:00 */
        date_sub(dtg, 0) as dtg,
        first(vessel_type_sub)
    from

    where

        and

    group by

        mmsi
)

paragraphs.title: Buy Gauge
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select 
    /* Calculate buy recommendataion */
    1 - sum(crude_tankers) over (order by dtg rows between 2 preceding and current row) as buy_guage,
    dtg,
    nyh_norm,
    usgc_norm
from (
    select 
        /* Calculate min/max normalized values */
        dtg,
        ((nyh - min_nyh) / (max_nyh - min_nyh)) as nyh_norm, 
        ((usgc - min_usgc) / (max_usgc - min_usgc)) as usgc_norm,
        ((avg_num_ships - min_avg_num_ships) / (max_avg_num_ships - min_avg_num_ships)) as crude_tankers
    from (
        select
            /* Prepare for min/max normalization */
            dtg,
            nyh,
            min(nyh) over () as min_nyh,
            max(nyh) over () as max_nyh,
            usgc,
            min(usgc) over () as min_usgc,
            max(usgc) over () as max_usgc,
            avg_num_ships,
            min(avg_num_ships) over () as min_avg_num_ships,
            max(avg_num_ships) over () as max_avg_num_ships
        from (
            /* Get from the JOIN */
            select 
                /* Fill null values with last value to make graph continuous */
                ifnull(gas.nyh_value, last(gas.nyh_value,true) over (order by ships.dtg)) as nyh,
                ifnull(gas.usgc_value, last(gas.usgc_value,true) over (order by ships.dtg)) as usgc,
                avg_num_ships,
                ships.dtg as dtg
            from (
                /* 3 day moving average of number of ships arriving at houston */
               select
                    dtg,
                    avg(count) over (order by dtg rows between 3 preceding and current row) as avg_num_ships
                from (
                    select
                        cur.dtg as dtg,
                        count(distinct cur.mmsi) as count
                    from 
                        tankers as cur
                    left join 
                        tankers as prev
                    on 
                        cur.dtg = date_add(prev.dtg, 1)
                        and cur.mmsi = prev.mmsi
                    where 
                        isnull(prev.mmsi)
                    group by 
                        cur.dtg
                ) 
            ) as ships 
            LEFT JOIN (
            /* Select the Gas prices by day */
                select 
                    date_sub(dtg, 0) as dtg_sub,
                    nyh as nyh_value,
                    usgc as usgc_value
                from 
                    gasPrices 
                where 
                    dtg > cast('2017-07-10T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp) 
                    and 
                    dtg < cast('2017-11-03T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp)
            ) as gas 
            on 
                ships.dtg = gas.dtg_sub
        )
    )
    where 
        /* Cut off lead dates that have null fuel values */
        dtg > cast('2017-07-17T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp) 
        and 
        dtg < cast('2017-11-3T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp)
    order by 
        dtg
)

paragraphs.title: Arrivals - Departures: Net change in number of tankers per day.
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select 
    arrivals.dtg as dtg,
    arr_count - dep_count as net_count
from (
    /* Arrivals */
    select
        dtg,
        count as arr_count
    from (
        select
            cur.dtg as dtg,
            count(distinct cur.mmsi) as count
        from 
            houston_ships as cur
        left join 
            houston_ships as prev
        on 
            cur.dtg = date_add(prev.dtg, 1)
            and cur.mmsi = prev.mmsi
        where 
            isnull(prev.mmsi)
        group by 
            cur.dtg
    ) 
    where
        /* Cut out extra data so we only have 1 month */
        dtg > cast('2017-07-17T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp) 
    order by 
        cur.dtg
) as arrivals 
left join (
    /* Departures */
    select 
        dtg,
        count as dep_count
    from (
        select
            prev.dtg as dtg,
            count(distinct prev.mmsi) as count
        from 
            houston_ships as cur
        right join 
            houston_ships as prev
        on 
            cur.dtg = date_add(prev.dtg, 1)
            and cur.mmsi = prev.mmsi
        where 
            isnull(cur.mmsi)
        group by 
            prev.dtg
    )
    where
        /* Cut out extra data so we only have 1 month */
        dtg > cast('2017-07-17T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp) 
    order by 
        prev.dtg
) as departures
on arrivals.dtg = departures.dtg
order by
    dtg

paragraphs.title: Temp View for tankers around Houston over harvey
paragraphs.text:
%sql

create or replace temp view houston_ships as 
select 
    mmsi,
    /* convert to 00:00:00 */
    date_sub(dtg, 0) as dtg,
    first(vessel_type_sub)
from (
    select 
        * 
    from  
        fsdsAIS 
    where 
        /* We need to over shoot the beginning by about a week so we don't have artifacts in the moving averages from null */
        dtg > cast('2017-01-01T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp) 
        and 
        dtg < cast('2017-12-26T00:00:00.000Z' as timestamp)
        and 
        st_intersects(st_makeBBOX(-100.3051, 15.5020, -73.6962, 33.8272), position) /* Gulf */
)
where
    st_contains(st_bufferPoint(st_makePoint(-94.867089, 29.580314), 50000), position) /* Houston */
    and
    vessel_type like "Tanker"
group by 
    dtg,
    mmsi
